   {:e #blake3 "78a168fb8116853428824082776e92da27eba9cb81d8547d0578b17cadbbeb81" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: main.rs opens LiveStore TWICE per command: Phase 1 (session auto-detect, writes session start tx, drops), Phase 3 (post-command hooks for RFL-2). Each open deserializes 92MB store.bin = ~300ms. Double open = guaranteed 600ms overhead per command.\n\nAPPROACH: Open LiveStore once at the top of main, pass a mutable reference through session auto-detect, command dispatch, and post-command hooks. The session auto-detect and RFL-2 hooks reuse the same handle. This requires threading LiveStore through the command dispatch, which means command functions take &mut LiveStore instead of opening their own. Moderate refactor but eliminates 300ms per command.\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) Only 1 LiveStore::open() call per CLI invocation. (B) Session auto-detect and post-command hooks both see the same store state. (C) All E2E tests pass. (D) Benchmark: ~300ms improvement per command.\n\nFILE: crates/braid/src/main.rs, command dispatch in crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs\nDEPENDS-ON: nothing directly, but benefits compound with P4-DAEMON (daemon makes this less critical). Wave 2." :op :assert}
